Left in-progress comments.
please pass error codes by const reference.  This reduces the number of intermediate constructions.
Done
Done
Why are we default constructing a message object here?  Having a default arg in a constructor seems odd.

Got rid of default constructing the message object and instead we will take pointer to just sd_bus_error. However, this requires explicitly passing 'nullptr' as argument where we don't rely on message. Also renamed getError() to more fitting getErrorMessage().
These are generally not what an error id would look like.  In normal openbmc dbus usage, an error would look like "xyz.openbmc_project.InvalidId" or something similar.

These are all fairly unsafe references.  Could we rearchitect these methods to simply take these as the first few arguments like we've done everywhere else, and remove the class entirely?

Having one class to verify all errors is a little worrisome, and not simple to trace.

After some thought I am not sure about removing the class entirely and moving to functions as having 3 extra arguments for each call would make the call context even bigger (see line #864). If it's still prefered way we can do this.

Line 864 should realistically be a real function now, and passed the context.

I would really like to avoid the class if we can because that kind of code on line 864 is very difficult to review.  It's calling 10 methods in a single branch.

Also, and more importantly, I don't know of anywhere else in the code that we handle errors using a class this large, so there would be a lot of rampup to make sure that it's correct and maintainable.

Removed ErrorVerification class for now. I am still looking for most efficient way to minimize the call context @ line 864 (where we could pass whole userArgs class to one 'verify-all' function and verify the fields there) BUT to still have it efficient and readable for other calls (for example @ line 1105, where we verify only some of the properties and they are not passed as object members).
lets avoid changing auto -> type in this case.  Although both are allowed, it's unrelated to the overall change.
?  This doesn't look related to error handling?
Moved this part to 'Add PUT and PATCH' patch

Right - I am working on this, the challenge is to make it work also with non-string parameters (appendLimit, reportActions). They all are eventually made string for message function - either we can cast them to string in calling context (but make it even more unreadable) or make verifyParameter agnostic of 'parameter' type  and deduce the type from errorMessage, but not sure about that (I have done this using template, not tested yet).
Looks like this error got dropped?  Any of these others we need to keep?
pass string_views by value.
I am not sure if name is necessary, and that's one extra thing to pass.

Each of these is checking against an error message that doesn't really follow the phosphor-dbus-interfaces naming convention, which would start with xyz.X.X.  I also don't see any errors called out here:

https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/master/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Telemetry/ReportManager.interface.yaml

What am i missing?
Please don't use starts_with.  this is called out in the coding standard.
Why do we create an empty array just do dump it?
Isn't this no longer correct if we're calling verify() in multiple places?
nit, please put each of these on their own line with their own branch.
Wouldn't the error here be a normal "path doesn't exist" error?  Rather than one that returns the ID?
